						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Summary-report-of-ReSAKSS-Africa-Lead-Project-on-Strengthening-Capacity-for-Strategic-Agricultural-Policy-and-Investment-Planning-and-Implementation-in-Africa" title="Summary report of ReSAKSS–Africa Lead Project on Strengthening Capacity for Strategic Agricultural Policy and Investment Planning and Implementation in Africa" alt="link">Summary report of ReSAKSS–Africa Lead Project on Strengthening Capacity for Strategic Agricultural Policy and Investment Planning and Implementation in Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>The five regional-level training workshops, which were organised in April and June 2012, provided training on the CAADP agenda, Strategic Analysis and Knowledge Support System (SAKSS) concepts, monitoring and evaluation, agricultural policy analysis and knowledge management tools. The gatherings were also used as a forum for discussing and sharing experiences that enhanced ideas on how country SAKSS can be designed in the different countries. Through discussions, participants identified country needs as far as SAKSS is concerned. This has already helped to improve the methodology and instruments used for undertaking the country SAKSS capacity needs assessments that were recently launched. The results of the assessments, hopefully, will help governments and stakeholders identify capacities, analytical tools, and information to generate credible, timely and high quality knowledge products to inform and guide agricultural sector policies and planning and review processes.(RekSASS, 28/8/2012)<a href="http://blog.resakss.org/2012/08/28/summary-report-of-the-five-regional-level-workshops-on-capacity-strengthening-released/" target="_blank">http://blog.resakss.org/2012/08/28/summary-report-of-the-five-regional-level-workshops-on-capacity-strengthening-released/</a></p>
